Credentials can be big, and they all go in the tree.  We should define a type of credential that is a secure indirection, something like:

```
enum {
    ...
    reference(xxx),
    ...
} CredentialType;

struct {
    opaque hash<0..255>;
    opaque uri<0..255>;
} CredentialReference;
```

With the provisos that: (1) the content reference by the URI MUST be a valid Credential struct, and MUST match the hash, and (2) it's up to the application to make sure that clients know how to deference the URIs.

