"Targeted message" seems to suggest that you might want to send a message to a _user_ rather than to a specific group member (where by user, I mean someone who might run multiple devices and thus be the entity behind more than one node in the group. Sorry if I got the official terminology wrong here). If that is the case, again, a proper sub-group might be the way to go. A quick-and-dirty way might be to just KEM to multiple leaf nodes, so that might also be an option (if there are not too many of them and targeted messages are an infrequent thing).

