You guys have an off-by-one error :)  This is the `init_secret` at the **output** of the current epoch's key schedule, not the input.  So it can't be used to derive the current epoch secret.

The whole reason that we have an `init_secret` (as opposed to chaining from one `epoch_secret` to the next) is so that you can give it to someone to allow them to initialize without giving away the current epoch secrets.  

@beurdouche not sure what you mean about going backward.  Key schedule is all HDKFing along, so it's not reversible.

