It's a question of where you separate the handshake keys from the application keys.  You want them to be separate to simplify the analysis, so that the implication always goes Handshake => Application and not vice versa.

In the current draft, the nearest common ancestor is the epoch secret.  I think you're on the right track here, and a better design would be to use the AStree to fan out secrets per participant, then split out different keys for different uses at the leaves.

